<br>
Unfortunately, I think it would be too difficult to realistically enforce.  The best compromise that I think could actually be enforced is a flat tax, as proposed by Steve Forbes and others.  If you want to have &quot;everyone pay their fair share&quot;, to me, this is a no brainer!  17 percent across the board is the number I've heard.  However, many Democrats oppose this because they are too stupid to understand what &quot;percent&quot; means and honestly believe that 17 percent of 20 grand and 17 percent of a million are the same dollar amount.<br>
